                      "Sankalp (Sacred Vow & Intention Declaration)",
                      "Ganesh Puja",
                      "Kalash Sthapana (Invocation of Divine Presence)",
                      "Invocation of Lord Shiva",
                      "Bilva Leaf Shiva Archana",
                      "Shiva Mantra Chanting",
                      "Lighting of Sacred Lamps",
                      "Aarti & Blessings"
                ],
                "outro": "Every step is performed with traditional Vedic discipline and heartfelt devotion - seeking Lord Shiva's most gracious blessings of peace, protection, and prosperity for the entire family."
          },
          {
                "title": "When is Kedareshwara Vratam Performed?",
                "intro": "",
                "paragraphs": [
                      "Kedareshwara Vratam is most traditionally observed during the auspicious month of Deepavali - particularly on Amavasya day, which is considered especially sacred for this vratam. As a pandit, I also recommend observing this vratam on Mondays - the most auspicious day of the week for Lord Shiva's worship - or on any spiritually significant occasion when the family wishes to seek his divine blessings. Many families observe this vratam together as a beautiful annual tradition - coming together with faith, devotion, and a heartfelt prayer for prosperity, peace, and lasting harmony in their home and family life."
